Privacy Policy for Smart Calculator

Last Updated: July 22, 2024

Thank you for choosing Smart Calculator. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our application. By using Smart Calculator, you consent to the data practices described in this policy.

1. Information We Collect

1.1. Personal Data
We do not collect any personal data such as your name, email address, phone number, or any other identifiable information.

1.2. Usage Data
We may collect information about your usage of the app, including:

The type of mobile device you use
Your mobile operating system
The type of mobile internet browser you use
Usage details such as access times and the pages or features of our app you use
1.3. Device Permissions
Depending on your device, Smart Calculator may request certain permissions that allow it to access your device data. These permissions are:

Internet access: Required for checking updates and fetching certain resources.
Storage access: Required for saving and retrieving your calculation history.
2. How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information to:

Improve our app and user experience
Understand how our app is used
Fix bugs and improve performance
Communicate with you regarding updates or changes to the app (if applicable)
3. Sharing Your Information

We do not share, sell, rent, or trade your information with third parties except as described below:

Service Providers: We may share information with third-party service providers who perform services for us, such as data analysis and app hosting, solely for the purpose of carrying out their work for us.
Legal Requirements: We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities.
4. Data Security

We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure.

5. Children's Privacy

Smart Calculator is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that we have inadvertently received personal information from a child under 13, we will delete such information from our records.

6. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy in the app. You are advised to review this Privacy

Policy periodically for any changes. Changes to this Privacy Policy are effective when they are posted in the app.

7. Your Consent

By using Smart Calculator, you consent to our Privacy Policy.

8. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

Email: support@smartcalculatorapp.com
Mailing Address: Smart Calculator, Privacy Department, 1234 App Street, Suite 100, Tech City, TC 56789
9. Data Retention

We will retain your information only for as long as is necessary for the purposes set out in this Privacy

Policy periodically for any changes. Changes to this Privacy Policy are effective when they are posted in the app.

7. Your Consent

By using Smart Calculator, you consent to our Privacy Policy.

8. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

Email: support@smartcalculator.com
Address: Smart Calculator Privacy Team, 123 Tech Avenue, Suite 100, Silicon Valley, CA 94043

Thank you for using Smart Calculator. We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring a safe and enjoyable experience.

9. Governing Law

This Privacy Policy is governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the United States. You agree that any dispute arising from or relating to the subject matter of this Privacy Policy shall be governed by the exclusive jurisdiction and venue of the courts of the United States.

10. User Rights

Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have certain rights regarding your personal data. These may include:

The right to access the information we hold about you.
The right to correct or update your information.
The right to request the deletion of your information.
The right to object to the processing of your information.
To exercise these rights, please contact us at the email or address provided above.

11. Third-Party Links

Our app may contain links to other websites or applications that are not operated by us. If you click on a third-party link, you will be directed to that third party's site.



